We have meeting invites to send out as part of sprint teams 

Key Points 

- Heartbeat of scrum, where ideas are turned into values 
- Fixed length events of one month or less to create consistency (1-4 weeks)
- A new sprint starts immediately after the conclusion of the previous sprint

- All the work neccessary to achieve the product goal 

Sprint Events 
- Sprint planning 
- Daily Scrum
- Sprint Review 
- Sprint Retrospective 


- Sprint is a container for all other scrum events 
- Each event in scrum is formal oppurtunity to inspect and adapt scrum artifacts 
- Missing events results on lost of oppurtunity to inspect & adapt 
- All events are held at same time & same place to reduce complexity 




